221
00:10:46,970 --> 00:10:48,350
Because his father is Dumas père.

222
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:51,050
Oh, I see.

223
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:53,510
So what's the book about?

224
00:10:55,010 --> 00:10:57,050
A love story
between a courtesan and a man.

225
00:10:57,470 --> 00:10:58,550
A love story?

226
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,140
Chen Changning,

227
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,350
are you thinking of getting a girlfriend?

228
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:05,180
No.

229
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:06,390
Don't talk nonsense.

230
00:11:06,710 --> 00:11:08,220
Nonsense? If you weren't,

231
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:09,300
why'd you read this?

232
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,970
It's not a romance novel.

233
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,140
Not a love story?

234
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:17,050
Then what's the ending?

235
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:20,720
The heroine is misunderstood
by the hero.

236
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,390
He regrets it too late,

237
00:11:22,970 --> 00:11:24,140
and she dies of illness.

238
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:26,300
It reflects the society....

239
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:27,220
Misunderstanding?

240
00:11:27,850 --> 00:11:28,890
Terminal illness...

241
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:31,720
You like this cliché drama?

242
00:11:32,350 --> 00:11:33,350
Zhu Niannian,

243
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,010
can you let me finish?

244
00:11:35,890 --> 00:11:36,730
Go on, then.

245
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:38,980
Come on.

246
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,600
Never mind.

247
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:41,680
I won't say more.

248
00:11:46,890 --> 00:11:47,760
Come here.

249
00:11:48,850 --> 00:11:50,550
You took so long in the shower,

250
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:52,050
so I had to awkwardly chat with him.

251
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:54,140
What did you talk about?

252
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,470
Listen, I asked him

253
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:56,390
who's hotter,

254
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:58,470
Fu Hongxue or Ye Kai?

255
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,890
He actually likes the one
who bathed in public.

256
00:12:01,970 --> 00:12:03,220
I tried to get him to watch TV,

257
00:12:03,350 --> 00:12:04,470
but he insisted on reading

258
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:06,430
that cliché romance novel. What is it?

259
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,300
(La Dame aux Camélias)

260
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:08,360
The Lady of the Camellias.

261
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,720
